content.description:
Pitch 1 is a thin-corner climb, all free. Has some thin face moves on the lower 1/3 (crux) and some thin finger jamming-laybacking in the upper 1/3. The middle section is a mix of hands and fingers.

This pitch tends to be dry even when nearby routes are wet.

Pitch 2 is all free (5.10).

Pitch 3 is aid.
content.protection: For P1, bring thin stoppers (e.g., down to RP #3 or ~3/16" width), some small cams (finger-tip size), one hand-sized cam, and mid-range stoppers. The first third of the pitch has three 3/8"bolts.
content.location: Midway between Jesters of Chaos and the Perverse Traverse. An obvious, white, left-facing corner.

content.description: Rappel in or... best yet, climb Wilman's pitch 1 & 2 to the Sky Ledge. There is a fixed line currently on Wilman's as we are cleaning it. The climb itself is mostly bolted. The FFA party used a yellow alien at the end to protect to the final moves. PG13 as the final bolt is somewhat strenuous to clip and could result in an awkward fall.
content.location: starts on nice ledge at the top of Wilman's Walkabout P2.

content.description:
P1 - Strenuous climbing 10d leads to a nice ledge.

P2 - Many 1.5 and 2 for this pitch supposedly the crux is the traverse move and it can be easily aided to bring the grade down to 11d.
content.protection: Large cams are useful on p1
content.location: The route is the first route you come to on the Cheeks.

content.description: O so short but o so stout! Slightly overhung climbing, that's kinda painful. Don't use the cheater stone for the full points. Named in honor of one of Index's most accomplished climber's.
content.location: Left of Jesters of Chaos. Short but steep and right on trail.
